subject: Add setUpRedfishRoute to all nodes in redfish
commitMessage:
Add setUpRedfishRoute to all nodes in redfish

For better or worse, the series ahead of this is making use of
setUpRedfishRoute to do the common "redfish specified" things that need
to be done for a connection, like header checking, filtering, and other
things.  In the current model, where BMCWEB_ROUTE is a common function
for all HTTP routes, this means we need to propagate this injection call
into the whole tree ahead of the requests being handled.

In a perfect world, we would invent something like a REDFISH_ROUTE
macro, but because macros are discouraged, the routes take a variadic
template of parameters, and each call to the route has a .privileges()
call in the middle, there's no good way to effect this change in a less
costly manner.  This was messaged both in the prior reviews, and on
discord sourcing improvements on this pattern, to which none arose.

Signed-off-by: Ed Tanous <edtanous@google.com>
Change-Id: Id29cc799e214edad41e48fc7ce6eed0521f90ecb

what the process is in your mind when certain resource wants to inject efficient handlers? Remove this call, implement their own handler?

How can we reduce duplicate codes?

Parse parameters functions for sure can be reused. And individual handling functions?

> what the process is in your mind when certain resource wants to inject efficient handlers? Remove this call, implement their own handler?

I had imagined any efficient handlers would be a different overload of this, given that will have to do some sort of registration about which parameters they plan on implementing.  This is most likely a discussion to have on a different patchset because I don't see that behavior changing this any.

> 
> How can we reduce duplicate codes?

I asked this on multiple forums (reviews and discord) and talk about the problems with this in the commit message.  If you have any ideas to deduplicate, I'm happy to hear them (although it would've been nice to see the ideas before I did all the work, but it is what it is).

> 
> Parse parameters functions for sure can be reused. And individual handling functions?

Like I said above, I had imagined there would be a different overload of this where a caller could "request" to handle certain params on their own, and that would bypass that level of query, but I haven't given this a ton of thought.  For some things, like expand, I think the checks that already exist would prevent re-running already expanded parameters, but for things like filter, I'm not as sure.

Unless this is going to change this patchset a bunch, I suspect we can work through that on discord, not in the context of this review.
